## Connection Management

### Pool Configuration

- Use a single async engine per application process
- Configure pool size based on deployment (start: `pool_size=5`, `max_overflow=10`)
- Set `pool_pre_ping=True` to detect stale connections
- Set statement timeout at connection or session level (default: 30s for API queries)

### Session Lifecycle

```python
# Pattern: request-scoped session via FastAPI dependency
async with session.begin():
    # read/write within one transaction when mutating
    ...
```

Rules:

- One transaction per use case mutation
- Never hold transactions open across external API calls (Stripe, email)
- Use `READ COMMITTED` (PostgreSQL default) unless a specific isolation level is documented

### Read Replicas

When read replicas are available:

- Route read-only reporting and analytics queries to replicas
- Never route writes or read-after-write consistency-sensitive reads to replicas
- Order confirmation and payment status checks must read from primary

