## Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Tables | plural snake_case | `order_lines` |
| Columns | snake_case | `created_at` |
| Primary keys | `id` | `BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY` |
| Foreign keys | `{entity}_id` | `product_id` |
| Indexes | `ix_{table}_{columns}` | `ix_orders_customer_id` |
| Unique constraints | `uq_{table}_{columns}` | `uq_carts_session_token` |
| Check constraints | `ck_{table}_{description}` | `ck_order_lines_quantity_positive` |

Never use quoted mixed-case identifiers.

---

## Standard Columns

Every transactional table includes:

```sql
created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
```

Soft-deleted entities add:

```sql
deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL
```

Optimistic locking on contested aggregates:

```sql
version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1
```

Audit-sensitive tables may add:

```sql
created_by UUID NULL REFERENCES customers(id),
updated_by UUID NULL REFERENCES customers(id)
```

---

## Data Types (Platform Defaults)

| Domain | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Money | `NUMERIC(19, 4)` | Never float |
| Currency | `CHAR(3)` | ISO 4217 |
| Timestamps | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Never `TIMESTAMP` without TZ |
| Status enums | `TEXT` + CHECK or lookup table | Avoid PG ENUM for evolving statuses |
| Slugs | `TEXT` + UNIQUE | URL-safe, indexed |
| JSON metadata | `JSONB` | Optional attributes only |
| Quantities | `INTEGER` or `NUMERIC` | Never float for inventory |

